    "created_at": "2020-12-15T18:28:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-12-15T18:28:30Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I would like this to be reverted. My reasons for this are twofold. On the one hand because this adds one extra message per slot `No duty until next epoch`  and `Next duty`  which makes 1) harder to read the log if you are looking for information and 2) requires space to keep these extra message every 12 second. \r\n\r\nOn the other hand this information is already included in the logs that prysm has by default at level info: The attestation and proposal roles are scheduled and logged every 6.4 minutes in the validator logs (e.g. `Attestation schedule`) and this includes the precise slot when your validator will be attesting/proposing. And the current slot is being logged every slot by the beacon `Synced new block`, contains epoch, slot and the position of the slot in the epoch. This is all that a user needs to know where he/she stands and when he/she will be attesting. \r\n\r\nI think that the benefits of this PR are minimal compared to the above problems. ",
