    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I don't generally disagree with @potuz assertions.  But I do want to ask couple questions for discussion\r\n1) Does the current 'Attestation Schedule' message, also show when your validator is scheduled for Proposal?\r\n  - My original intent was to have a way of mitigating losing on such a once in a while event, which was more profitable for the validator because of an upgrade restart or other server maintenance\r\n 2) If it does, I am still thinking that in the case of multiple validators (imagine like 20 or 30), you still have to fish for this info to know if you're \"safe\" restarting your process.  In such cases, the next duty line, summarizing when you're supposed to work again, regardless of which validator it is, comes in very handy.\r\n\r\nHaving all that raised for discussion.  Perhaps there is room to make this logging facility a flag, and having it turned ``off`` by default.  \r\n\r\nAlso, if it is determined that this logging is verbose and pointless.  I would like to suggest perhaps, turning it into a prometheus consumable metric.   I think that will be valuable and leaves the decision of whether one wants to waste the space on it or not, entirely within the end user's hands.",
