    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": ">\r\n> 1. Does the current 'Attestation Schedule' message, also show when your validator is scheduled for Proposal?\r\n> \r\nYes it does, there's a log message `Proposal schedule`\r\n \r\n> 1. If it does, I am still thinking that in the case of multiple validators (imagine like 20 or 30), you still have to fish for this info to know if you're \"safe\" restarting your process.  In such cases, the next duty line, summarizing when you're supposed to work again, regardless of which validator it is, comes in very handy.\r\n\r\nIn case you have 20 - 30 validators then it doesn't matter, you will have duties throghout the epoch. In any case, there is going to be one message for each proposal slot (with multiple indexes if you have more than one validator proposing in that slot) and similar for attestations. \r\n\r\n> Also, if it is determined that this logging is verbose and pointless. I would like to suggest perhaps, turning it into a prometheus consumable metric. I think that will be valuable and leaves the decision of whether one wants to waste the space on it or not, entirely within the end user's hands.\r\n\r\nThis will be even worse, the prometheus db will increase dramatically having this on a per-pubkey basis. Prometheus keeps values of every single scrap. \r\n\r\nEDIT: On prometheus perhaps it won't be too dramatic to expose the slot of the duties, this would be only once per epoch per pubkey.  ",
