    "body": "> > This will be even worse, the prometheus db will increase dramatically having this on a per-pubkey basis. Prometheus keeps values of every single scrap.\r\n> > EDIT: On prometheus perhaps it won't be too dramatic to expose the slot of the duties, this would be only once per epoch per pubkey.\r\n> \r\n> There is no need for per public key. You only want to know when you're about to take an action. It doesn't matter per public key, since it's an all or nothing. One metric, with the next slot you're scheduled to have any kind of duty on. Preferably two, one with `next_attestation_slot` and one with `next_proposal_slot`.\r\n\r\nThat would be useless for the purpose you want it: validators get assigned a duty at epoch transitions. Consider you have two validators, on epoch start they are assigned on duties as follows.  The first validator is assigned on slot M to to attest. The second validator is assigned on slot M+1 to propose. In this circumstances you won't have any notice of the proposition. ",
